%description:
Regression test for RSVP-TE ResvErr (RFC 2205 Section 3.5): when an existing
reservation is preempted, the router doing the preempting sends a ResvErr
downstream toward the egress, and the egress processes it by logging and
removing its own local reservation state for the errored flow.

Reuses the examples/mpls/testte_reroute network (RSVPTE4) and its stock
LSR1_rsvp.xml priorities (unlike rsvpte_cac.test, which strips them to test
pure CAC bandwidth sharing without preemption):
  - tunnel 1, lsp 100, 400k, setup_pri=1/holding_pri=1 (better/higher priority),
    over LSR1->LSR3->LSR7->LSR5
  - tunnel 2, lsp 200, 400k, default setup_pri=7/holding_pri=7 (worst/lowest
    priority), over LSR1->LSR2->LSR4->LSR5

At t=2s a second path is added to tunnel 1 (lsp 101, 400k), also inheriting
tunnel 1's setup_pri=1, routed over LSR1->LSR2->LSR4->LSR5 -- the same links
tunnel 2 uses. Since lsp 101's setup priority (1) is better than tunnel 2's
holding priority (7), admitting it preempts tunnel 2's reservation instead of
being rejected (contrast with rsvpte_cac.test, where both sessions share the
same low priority and the higher-bandwidth request is rejected instead).

Before this commit, RsvpTe::preempt() silently zeroed the preempted RSB's
bandwidth and relied on the RSB's own soft-state timeout to eventually notice
-- it never sent anything, so the "sending ResvErr" and "reservation failed"
lines below never appeared, and processRSVPMessage's dispatch had no
RTEAR_MESSAGE/RERROR_MESSAGE cases at all (both fell into the `default:`
`throw`). This test fails on the parent commit because those log lines are
simply never produced -- there is nothing to send or receive.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: test.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../examples;../../../../src
network = inet.examples.mpls.testte_reroute.RSVPTE4
sim-time-limit = 3s
total-stack = 64MiB
record-vector-results = false
cmdenv-express-mode = false
**.cmdenv-log-level = "info"

**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host1.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host1.app[0].destAddresses = "host3"

**.host2.numApps = 1
**.host2.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host2.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host2.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host2.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host2.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host2.app[0].destAddresses = "host4"

**.host{3..4}.numApps = 1
**.host{3..4}.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host{3..4}.app[0].localPort = 100

**.host1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host1.rt"
**.host2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host2.rt"
**.host3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host3.rt"
**.host4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host4.rt"
**.host5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host5.rt"

**.LSR1.classifier.config = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR1_fec.xml")
**.LSR1.rsvp.traffic = xmldoc("LSR1_rsvp.xml")

**.LSR*.rsvp.helloInterval = 0.2s
**.LSR*.rsvp.helloTimeout = 0.5s

**.LSR1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR1.rt"
**.LSR2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR2.rt"
**.LSR3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR3.rt"
**.LSR4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR4.rt"
**.LSR5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR5.rt"
**.LSR6.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR6.rt"
**.LSR7.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR7.rt"

**.ppp[*].queue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.ppp[*].queue.packetCapacity = 10

**.scenarioManager.script = xmldoc("scenario.xml")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: LSR1_rsvp.xml
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<sessions>
	<session>
		<endpoint>host3</endpoint>
		<tunnel_id>1</tunnel_id>

		<setup_pri>1</setup_pri>
		<holding_pri>1</holding_pri>

		<paths>
			<path>
				<lspid>100</lspid>

				<bandwidth>400000</bandwidth>
				<route>
					<node>LSR1%routerId</node>
					<node>LSR3%routerId</node>
					<node>LSR7%routerId</node>
					<node>LSR5%routerId</node>
				</route>

				<permanent>true</permanent>
			</path>
		</paths>
	</session>
	<session>
		<endpoint>host4</endpoint>
		<tunnel_id>2</tunnel_id>

		<paths>
			<path>
				<lspid>200</lspid>

				<bandwidth>400000</bandwidth>
				<route>
					<node>LSR1%routerId</node>
					<node>LSR2%routerId</node>
					<node>LSR4%routerId</node>
					<node>LSR5%routerId</node>
				</route>

				<permanent>true</permanent>
			</path>
		</paths>
	</session>
</sessions>

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: scenario.xml
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<scenario>
	<at t="2s">
		<add-session module="LSR1.rsvp">
			<endpoint>host3</endpoint>
			<tunnel_id>1</tunnel_id>

			<paths>
				<path>
					<lspid>101</lspid>

					<bandwidth>400000</bandwidth>
					<route>
						<node>LSR1%routerId</node>
						<node>LSR2%routerId</node>
						<node>LSR4%routerId</node>
						<node>LSR5%routerId</node>
					</route>

				</path>
			</paths>
		</add-session>
	</at>
</scenario>

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Sanity: the add-session reached the ingress and tried to create the new (better-priority) path.
%contains: stdout
adding new path into an existing session
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# The preempting LSR sends a ResvErr downstream toward the egress for the RSB it just zeroed.
%contains: stdout
sending ResvErr (RSB
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# The egress processes the ResvErr: logs the failure and removes its own reservation state.
%contains: stdout
reservation failed (errorCode=
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
